MENINGITIS, VIRAL - ROMANIA (NORTHEAST): ECHOVIRUS
*****************************************
A ProMED post
<http://www.healthnet.org/programs/promed.html>
See Also
Meningitis, viral - Romania (northeast), Moldova 990819120558
Meningitis, viral - Romania (NE), Moldova: Correction
990822231628
Meningitis, viral - Hungary ex Romania? 990819123712
Date: Mon 30 Aug 1999 12:25:09 +0300 (EEST)
From: Official Mailbox <office@mails.cantacuzino.ro>

Concerning the epidemic you are interested in:
- About 750 cases of mild meningitis (clear csf) [CSF =
cerebrospinal fluid were recorded in about 2 months (July - Aug
1999) mainly in the northeast part of Romania: Botosani, Suceava,
Iasi, Bacau counties.
- Subjects: children 4-15 years of age.
- Three different echo type viruses were isolated and identified:
4, 7 & 30.
- The attack rate is decreasing.
--
Marian Negut
Director
Cantacuzino Institute
Bucharest
Romania
<office@mails.cantacuzino.ro>
[We are very grateful to Dr Negut for this official report. Note that the
number of cases is considerably lower than the thousands in some
media reports. Echovirus types 7 & 30 have also been implicated in
epidemics of viral meningitis in the USA - Mod.JW
...........................................jw
